article.headline: UTEP 78, Rice 64
article.story: EL PASO, Texas -- Jeremy Williams hit 6 of 7 3-pointers and scored 20 points as UTEP defeated Rice, 78-64, in Conference USA play on Saturday night. Randy Culpepper hit four 3's and finished the game with 18 points. The Miners (22-5, 13-1) hit 12 of 25 (48.0 percent) from 3-point range. The Owls (8-20, 1-13) were not as hot from long range hitting just 6 of 19 (31.6 percent). Arsalan Kazemi led Rice with 12 points. Lawrence Ghoram added 11 points. Williams hit a 3-pointer with just 3-seconds left in the first half to give the Miners a 45-34 halftime lead. The Miners were leading 62-48 with 12:02 left when they went on an 11-0 run to lead 73-48 and put the game away for sure. UTEP finished in first place in the conference, while the Owls finished 12th (last).
